snippet.title: CALL OF DUTY: INIFINITE WARFARE · JACKAL ASSAULT VR Gameplay | PSVR PS4 VR
snippet.description:
Call of Duty: Infinite Warfare Jackal Assault VR Experience gameplay in 1080p 60fps.  Available now on the PSN store for free, requires Playstation VR (PSVR).  Impressions - you can use head-tracking to acquire targets to shoot missiles.  I didn't have as much motion sickness as I did here than RIGS (which also uses head-tracking) which I could not stomach.  I think the graphics looked better than Eve Valkyrie, at least in the demo I tried.  Eve is much blurrier.  Can't really complain when it's free, but I don't think I'll mess with it again.  

Enjoy the videos? Hit the 💗LIKE💖 button! It's your way to help support the channel!

Call of Duty: Infinite Warfare Description:
Call of Duty: Infinite Warfare delivers something for every Call of Duty fan with three unique game modes: Campaign, Multiplayer, and Zombies. Delivering a rich and engaging narrative in a setting unlike anything to date in a Call of Duty game, the campaign is a return to the franchise’s gritty, military roots throughout new environments never before seen in the franchise.

Developer: Infinity Ward
Publisher: Activision
Platform: PC, PlayStation 4, Xbox One
Release date: November 4, 2016
Genre: First-person shooter
Mode: Single-player, multiplayer
